<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870413-0130 </DOCNO><HL> LTV Subsidiary Receives$80 Million Army Contract</HL><DD> 04/13/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> LTV GQ GM HON GMHDEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Aerospace andamp; Defense Co., an LTV Corp. unit, received an $80 million Army contract for research on ballistic missile defense systems.    Grumman Corp. was awarded a $66.9 million addition to a Navy contract for E2C aircraft.    Hughes Aircraft Co., a General Motors Corp. unit, won $66.8 million in Army and Navy contracts for electronics equipment and parts for armored vehicles.    Honeywell Inc.'s Defense Systems division got a $34.7 million Army contract for artillery-projectile parts. </TEXT></DOC>